able and unimaginable - nuclear apocalypse - imaginable. The book will be required reading for everyone who wants to understand the cultural dynamics of the Cold War through the angle of its core ingredient, nuclear weapons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCold War in popular culture. 0aCold War. 0aImaginary wars and battles. 0aNuclear warfarexSocial aspects. 0aWar. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aCold War.  aSoviet Union.  aThird World War.  aUSA.  aatomic bomb.  apostwar Europe.1 aBoyer, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDawsey, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobson, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerster, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrant, Matthew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHorn, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKemper, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNowak, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubinson, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherif, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZiemann, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZiemann, Benjamin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610132740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526101327423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526101